# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Ingestion environment — example. Copy to `.env` (which is git-ignored).
#
# SOURCE POLICY (Neha, 2026-06-05): OFFICIAL-FIRST and LOGIN-FREE.
#   - Core data comes from IRDAI / GI Council / NSE-BSE / company public
#     disclosures. None of these need a login.
#   - Screener / Trendlyne / Investing are used only as clearly-tagged,
#     low-confidence BACKUP for cells with no official equivalent, and only via
#     their public (no-login) pages.
#   - Therefore NO site credentials are required, and none should be committed.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Set to 0 in CI (which has internet egress) to fetch live. Default/offline (1
# or unset) replays whatever is staged under data/raw/, so local runs work too.
INGEST_OFFLINE=0

# OPTIONAL escape hatch for sources that block DATACENTER IPs at the network
# level (IRDAI and NSE return a standing 403 to GitHub Actions even through
# headless Chrome). Point this at an in-region / residential fetch relay that
# accepts the literal {url} placeholder. Leave unset to disable.
# This is NOT a paywall/CAPTCHA bypass — it only changes the egress IP.
# INGEST_FETCH_PROXY=https://your-relay.example/fetch?target={url}

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# If you ever decide to switch a backup source to authenticated access, add the
# secret HERE (and as a GitHub Actions secret) — never in code. The adapters do
# not read these today (login-free mode); they are placeholders for that choice.
# SCREENER_SESSION_COOKIE=
# TRENDLYNE_SESSION_COOKIE=
# INVESTING_SESSION_COOKIE=
